WEBVTT

1
00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.389
You must do something.
Baby's coming.

2
00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:02.155
Yeah. I know. Miss. you have to
stay calm and take deep breaths.

3
00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:03.958
Myra. I need a doctor here now.

4
00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:06.873
- I'm working on it.
- You're not doctor?

5
00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:09.190
- I'm a nurse.
- You are man and you are nurse?

6
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:11.396
What kind of man is nurse?

7
00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:14.790
Look. folks. I'm a professional. OK?
I know what I'm doing.

8
00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:17.519
Trust me. everything's going to be fine.

9
00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:19.716
Yeah.
Yeah. you're fully dilated.

10
00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:21.870
Hey. I need that doctor right now.

11
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:25.396
There are no free doctors.
You'll have to deliver the baby.

12
00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:27.994
I can see a head.

13
00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:30.389
Holy shit.

14
00:01:36.440 --> 00:01:39.477
Check it out. We did it.

15
00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:41.551
We had a boy.

16
00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:45.836
A boy. You're my hero.

17
00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:49.151
- I name a baby for you.
- You don't have to do that.

18
00:01:49.240 --> 00:01:53.438
I must. It's a Latvian tradition.
We will name the baby...

19
00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:06.914
You've reached the Fockers.
We're not around.

20
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:08.991
so leave a message. Goodbye.

21
00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:12.231
Roz. How the hell
do you shut this thing off?

22
00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:14.311
I have no idea. Just press a button.

23
00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:17.392
I'm pretty sure it's off.
Honey. you want a chimichanga?

24
00:02:17.480 --> 00:02:20.677
- They give you gas.
- A little. but it's worth it.

25
00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:22.876
For you.
I'm the one that gets the fumes.

26
00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:26.077
- I'm in the mood for a chimichanga.
- So make a...

27
00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:27.752
Hey. guys. it's me.

28
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.991
Dad. I told you six months ago
to change that message.

29
00:02:31.080 --> 00:02:33.958
I'm calling to double check.
cos I didn't hear from you.

30
00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:36.349
Pam and I are flying out
to Oyster Bay today.

31
00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:38.749
then to Miami tomorrow
with the Byrneses.

32
00:02:38.840 --> 00:02:41.991
We get in at 7.30. That should
put us at the house around 9.00.

33
00:02:42.080 --> 00:02:43.911
So give me a call back
on my cell.

34
00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.913
I want to go over a few things
with you about Pam's dad and

35
00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.673
some other stuff for the weekend.
Love you. Bye.

36
00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:52.876
- Hey.
- Morning. How was your shift?

37
00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:54.791
- Guess what.
- What?

38
00:02:54.880 --> 00:02:57.394
- I delivered my first baby.
- No way.

39
00:02:57.480 --> 00:03:00.233
- Honey. I'm so proud of you.
- It was incredible.

40
00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:04.199
I mean. just to be pulling
this life force out of this woman's...

41
00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:08.068
You know. It was just so...
The whole baby thing is...

42
00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:10.799
- It's so cool.
- That's great. honey.

43
00:03:10.880 --> 00:03:13.075
- That's great.
- So. you ready to go?

44
00:03:13.160 --> 00:03:15.196
- I want to get to the airport.
- In a sec.

45
00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:17.669
- Things always go wrong.
- We have four hours.

46
00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:21.070
I wish we could set a wedding date
without our parents meeting.

47
00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:23.071
This weekend is going to be fine.

48
00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:26.197
- Your parents are great.
- They're great in small doses.

49
00:03:26.280 --> 00:03:30.637
48 hours in Coconut Grove is a small
dose. Besides. you've won over my dad.

50
00:03:30.720 --> 00:03:32.676
And that is the hard part.

51
00:03:32.760 --> 00:03:36.309
It is true. I am still in the
Byrnes family Circle of Trust.

52
00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:38.994
You're firmly in the Circle.

53
00:03:39.320 --> 00:03:40.309
Finally.

54
00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:44.278
- Taxi.
- Taxi.

55
00:03:49.200 --> 00:03:50.952
- You going to the airport?
- Yeah.

56
00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:53.076
- Take mine.
- All right.

57
00:03:53.160 --> 00:03:55.310
Great.

58
00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:01.354
- Nice guy. huh?
- Yeah.

59
00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:19.432
You two. you're up.

60
00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:44.875
- Oh. dear.
- What?

61
00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:47.793
Well. they overbooked coach.

62
00:04:47.880 --> 00:04:51.236
So what does that mean?
Do we miss our flight. or...

63
00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:54.835
Well. we are gonna
have to upgrade you to first class.

64
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.070
Really?

65
00:04:57.160 --> 00:04:58.718
Thank you.

66
00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:03.597
Sir. why don't you
let me take that for you?

67
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.511
OK. Yeah.

68
00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:11.388
You wanna check it? Or put it
on another flight? That's cool.

69
00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:13.914
Just gonna store it
in the captain's closet.

70
00:05:16.640 --> 00:05:19.108
- That was nice.
- Yeah.

71
00:05:19.200 --> 00:05:21.395
- Champagne?
- Thank you.

72
00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:24.199
- Champagne. sir?
- Thank you.

73
00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:26.032
Enjoy.

74
00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:36.557
Would you like to purchase
rental insurance. Mr Focker?

75
00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:39.674
No.

76
00:05:39.760 --> 00:05:42.194
- Thanks.
- No?

77
00:05:42.280 --> 00:05:45.272
It's a scam.
That's how they make all their money.

78
00:05:45.360 --> 00:05:47.351
That's true. You don't need it.

79
00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:50.396
Get outta here.

80
00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:05.475
The house of Byrnes.

81
00:06:06.440 --> 00:06:08.795
A lot of good memories here.

82
00:06:09.880 --> 00:06:11.791
Mom? Dad?

83
00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:15.034
I am watching you.

84
00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:18.911
Almost.

85
00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.036
But you have to do it
with two fingers.

86
00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:23.190
one on each eye. like this.

87
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:25.316
I am watching you.

88
00:06:26.960 --> 00:06:29.713
We'll get back to that later.
Guess who's here?

89
00:06:29.800 --> 00:06:32.519
It's Professor Einstein.

90
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.239
Hi. Little Jack.
You are a genius.

91
00:06:35.320 --> 00:06:37.993
I see a Nobel Prize in your future.
Yes. I do.

92
00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:40.674
Study break. boys.
Company's here.

93
00:06:41.560 --> 00:06:43.915
- Pamcake.
- Flapjack.

94
00:06:45.960 --> 00:06:47.996
Short stack.
short stack. coming up.

95
00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:50.799
Put some syrup in the cup.

96
00:06:55.400 --> 00:06:57.595
That's how it goes. right?

97
00:06:57.680 --> 00:06:59.033
That's OK. Greg.

98
00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:01.509
- Nice to see you.
- Yes.

99
00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:04.956
- Nice to see you. Grandpa.
- Yeah.

100
00:07:05.040 --> 00:07:08.635
My goodness. How did my nephew
get so big? Look at you.

101
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:11.757
- You look just like your mommy.
- He does. doesn't he?

102
00:07:11.840 --> 00:07:15.435
Hey. this is Greg.
Remember we talked about him?

103
00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:24.998
Sorry. Greg.
The card only comes in one gender.

104
00:07:25.680 --> 00:07:27.671
Yeah. no. that's all right.

105
00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:30.278
He's taking you in.

106
00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.920
He has a very keen sense
for people. Greg.

107
00:07:34.200 --> 00:07:36.077
A chip off the old block. huh?

108
00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:38.310
Might have another CIA man
on our hands.

109
00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:41.119
I'd be discreet about my profession
if I were you.

110
00:07:41.200 --> 00:07:44.510
As far as your parents are concerned.
I'm a horticulturalist.

111
00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:47.478
Are Deb and Bob house-sitting
while we're in Florida?

112
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:48.993
No. they're in Thailand.

113
00:07:49.080 --> 00:07:51.878
visiting the clinic
they opened on their honeymoon.

114
00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:54.076
What is all this stuff. anyway?

115
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:56.833
After Denny was sent away
to military school.

116
00:07:56.920 --> 00:08:00.799
your father turned this into
a learning laboratory for you-know-who.

117
00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:03.917
Can't you talk yet.
Mr Munchkin Head. you little...

118
00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:12.236
Greg. Greg. don't infantilise him.
Talk to him like an adult.

119
00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:14.072
Muskrat.

120
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:16.754
- Muskrat. Jack.
- Right.

121
00:08:16.840 --> 00:08:19.115
Try to understand. he's a little person.

122
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:23.193
His communication skills aren't verbal
yet. but he understands. Observe.

123
00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.116
LJ. are you hungry?

124
00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:33.998
Look at that.

125
00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:39.108
"I would like to eat more. please."

126
00:08:39.200 --> 00:08:43.398
"I'd like a nap. and then later
I'll enjoy a nice poop."

127
00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:50.509
I've heard about
this baby signing stuff.

128
00:08:50.600 --> 00:08:52.989
This is. like. cutting edge.
Like... yeah.

129
00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:55.799
At his age. Greg.
his mind is like a sponge.

130
00:08:55.880 --> 00:08:57.836
But when he reaches your age.

131
00:08:57.920 --> 00:09:00.992
his mind will be less capable
of absorbing information.

132
00:09:01.080 --> 00:09:03.469
He's so cute. Can I hold him?

133
00:09:03.560 --> 00:09:05.949
I don't think that's
such a good idea. Greg.

134
00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.792
Muskrat.

135
00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:11.356
All right. All right.

136
00:09:11.440 --> 00:09:15.035
This is Greg.
Greg will not drop you. OK?

137
00:09:16.280 --> 00:09:17.554
OK.

138
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.518
- Be careful.
- Hello. Hello.

139
00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:25.311
I think he likes me.

140
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:26.799
No?

141
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:30.275
- Shit.
- Focker.

142
00:09:30.360 --> 00:09:31.793
He's absorbing you.

143
00:09:31.880 --> 00:09:34.519
I don't want his first word
to be a profanity.

144
00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:38.229
It's OK. Cover your nose.
You're terrifying him.

145
00:09:38.320 --> 00:09:41.039
- I'll get a towel.
- Focker.

146
00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:43.714
Cool how your dad's
so into being a grandparent.

147
00:09:43.800 --> 00:09:47.588
I think it freaks my mom out. He spends
every last second with that kid.

148
00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:51.119
Oh. my God.

149
00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:54.198
Daddy?

150
00:09:55.600 --> 00:09:57.830
Daddy. what is this thing?

151
00:09:57.920 --> 00:09:59.672
A custom-designed motor coach.

152
00:09:59.760 --> 00:10:02.320
Jack calls it the
"Highlight of our Twilight".

153
00:10:04.880 --> 00:10:07.997
- This is incredible.
- Isn't it?

154
00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:11.559
It's like a tank.

155
00:10:11.640 --> 00:10:15.428
In these uncertain times.
I opted for a Kevlar-reinforced hull

156
00:10:15.520 --> 00:10:18.159
with two-inch thick Plexiglas windows.

157
00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:20.879
like on the Russian
Widowmaker submarines.

158
00:10:20.960 --> 00:10:23.554
I want you to conduct
a field test for us. Greg.

159
00:10:23.640 --> 00:10:27.792
I want you to demonstrate the
impregnable outer skin of the coach.

160
00:10:27.880 --> 00:10:29.871
Throw it at the window.

161
00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:33.678
Jack. I'm not gonna throw
a brick at your window.

162
00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:35.716
- It's a simple demonstration.
- No.

163
00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:38.678
- Throw the brick. Greg.
- OK. Just...

164
00:10:38.760 --> 00:10:40.432
- All your might.
- All right.

165
00:10:47.400 --> 00:10:50.437
Don't worry. Your rental insurance
will take care of it.

166
00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:51.509
Jack?

167
00:10:51.600 --> 00:10:54.797
Come on.
We'll call a tow truck from the road.

168
00:10:54.880 --> 00:10:58.270
- The road?
- Yeah. we're driving this to Miami.

169
00:10:58.360 --> 00:11:00.396
I thought we were flying tomorrow.

170
00:11:00.480 --> 00:11:04.075
No. Airline travel being what
it is these days. so unreliable.

171
00:11:04.160 --> 00:11:07.755
I'll feel more comfortable knowing
I have my own Posturepedic bed.

172
00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:10.308
my own thermostat.
my own lavatory facility.

173
00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:13.475
So we're all gonna be in this together?

174
00:11:13.560 --> 00:11:17.712
We hit the road in exactly
seven minutes. 27 seconds.

175
00:11:17.800 --> 00:11:21.793
This way we'll get in early. spend
an extra half-day with your parents.

176
00:11:21.880 --> 00:11:24.474
- Isn't that great?
- That is great.

177
00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:26.630
...but I'm the one
that gets the fumes.

178
00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:30.030
- I'm in the mood for a chimichanga.
- So make a...

179
00:11:30.120 --> 00:11:32.793
Hey. guys. it's me.

180
00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:36.077
I'm getting worried that
I haven't heard back from you.

181
00:11:36.160 --> 00:11:40.119
There's been a little change of plans.
We're coming down in Jack's RV.

182
00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:43.749
We'll be arriving tomorrow afternoon.
not tomorrow night.

183
00:11:43.840 --> 00:11:47.628
OK. tomorrow afternoon. And they're
bringing their little grandson.

184
00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:52.077
So... He's a baby.
so... I don't know.

185
00:11:53.160 --> 00:11:55.196
Welcome aboard. me hearties.

186
00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:56.838
This is incredible.

187
00:11:56.920 --> 00:11:59.639
- It's as big as our apartment.
- Pretty neat. huh?

188
00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:06.672
Mr Jinx finally learned
how to flush the toilet. huh?

189
00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:11.629
Yeah. Jack installed a special flusher
and he learned in about two days.

190
00:12:11.720 --> 00:12:13.597
Hey there. Jinxy.
How are you doing?

191
00:12:18.200 --> 00:12:20.794
Ready to hit the road. Co-Captain?

192
00:12:22.040 --> 00:12:24.952
- I'm the co-captain?
- Let's set sail. sailor.

193
00:12:28.600 --> 00:12:30.318
Good afternoon.

194
00:12:30.400 --> 00:12:32.436
This is Captain Jack Byrnes speaking.

195
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:35.036
- Daddy.
- A quick announcement.

196
00:12:35.120 --> 00:12:37.315
As a courtesy to fellow passengers.

197
00:12:37.400 --> 00:12:40.756
the on-board lavatory
should be used for number one only.

198
00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:42.671
Should a need for number two arise.

199
00:12:42.760 --> 00:12:45.399
we'll stop at a rest stop
or a heavily wooded area.

200
00:12:45.480 --> 00:12:47.391
Thank you. Welcome aboard.

201
00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:51.871
I like that thing. You mind
if I make a little announcement?

202
00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:54.952
Well. only the captain
gets to make an announcement.

203
00:12:56.640 --> 00:12:58.437
Do you want to honk the horn?

204
00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:00.829
Sure.

205
00:13:00.920 --> 00:13:02.956
Only the captain gets to honk the horn.

206
00:13:10.680 --> 00:13:11.999
Look.

207
00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:13.513
Hey. Jinxy. See that?

208
00:13:19.200 --> 00:13:21.430
LJ. are you hungry.
do you want some milk?

209
00:13:25.640 --> 00:13:27.790
Hey. Jack.

210
00:13:28.840 --> 00:13:31.400
- She wants you to honk the horn.
- Not interested.

211
00:13:32.160 --> 00:13:34.515
Rules of the road.
She honks. you honk.

212
00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:37.672
Come on. Jack. Give her a honk.

213
00:13:37.760 --> 00:13:39.557
There you go.

214
00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:42.598
Yeah. Hey. Looks like a team
or something.

215
00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:45.877
"Honk if you're horny."

216
00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:54.876
Thanks for that. Greg.

217
00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:03.193
I'm the one that gets the fumes.

218
00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:05.999
- I'm in the mood for a chimichanga.
- So make a...

219
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:13.152
Hey. there.

220
00:14:14.040 --> 00:14:16.315
No hard feelings. all right?

221
00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:18.197
Friends?

222
00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:20.475
What's that?
What are you saying?

223
00:14:20.560 --> 00:14:23.711
Wait a minute. What does this mean?
I know what this means.

224
00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:26.268
Squeeze. squeeze. squeeze. Poop.

225
00:14:26.360 --> 00:14:29.033
You gotta poop? OK. Good.
Thank you for warning me.

226
00:14:29.120 --> 00:14:32.430
Everybody poops. Sometimes it hurts.
It's OK. Just let it...

227
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:34.750
Let it come out.

228
00:14:34.840 --> 00:14:37.593
- What did you do?
- Nothing. I think he has to poop.

229
00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:40.433
That's not the sign for poop.
It's the sign for milk.

230
00:14:40.520 --> 00:14:43.432
- This is the poop sign.
- What's the sign for sour milk?

231
00:14:43.520 --> 00:14:45.511
This tastes a little funky.

232
00:14:45.600 --> 00:14:48.034
Because that's from
Debbie's left breast.

233
00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:56.118
She pumped for a week
to give us enough for the trip.

234
00:14:56.200 --> 00:15:00.398
- OK. snack pack for Little Jack.
- What are you doing there?

235
00:15:00.480 --> 00:15:02.675
During the breast-feeding stage. Greg.

236
00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:05.957
infants can get confused
when separated from their mothers.

237
00:15:06.040 --> 00:15:10.192
So I invented something to ease
LJ's anxiety during chow time.

238
00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:15.359
I call it the Manary Gland.

239
00:15:15.440 --> 00:15:18.750
I had it made from an exact cast
of Debbie's left bosom.

240
00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:23.276
Oh. yeah. OK.

241
00:15:23.360 --> 00:15:26.750
It's been so effective.
I'm thinking of getting it patented.

242
00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:29.354
- Would you like to touch it?
- I wouldn't.

243
00:15:29.440 --> 00:15:32.637
